<exercise number="19"><statement><p>The diagonal of a rectangle is 20 inches. The width of the rectangle is 4 inches shorter than its length.<ol label="a">  
    <li>Write a quadratic equation about the length of the rectangle.</li>
    <li>Solve your equation to find the dimensions of the rectangle.</li></ol></p></statement>
<answer><p><ol label="a">
    <li><m>L^2+(L-4)^2=20^2</m></li>
    <li>12 in by 16 in</li></ol></p>
</answer></exercise>

<exercise number="20"><statement><p>A box is made from a square piece of cardboard by cutting 2-inch squares from each corner and turning up the edges.</p>
<sidebyside  width="60%"><image source="images/fig-hw-3-4-20"><description>box</description></image></sidebyside>
<p><ol label="a">
    <li>If the piece of cardboard is <m>x</m> inches square, write expressions for the length, width and height of the box. Then write an expression for the volume <m>V</m> of the box in terms of <m>x</m>.</li>
    <li>Graph your expression for the volume on your calculator. What is the smallest value of <m>x</m> that makes sense for this problem?  Why?</li>
    <li>Write and solve a quadratic equation to answer the question:  What size cardboard do you need to make a box with volume 50 cubic inches?</li></ol></p>
</statement></exercise>

